        </h1>
        <div class="flex items-center text-lg mb-8">
          <time datetime="2026-03-20">March 20, 2026</time>
          <span class="mx-4">&bull;</span>
          <span>13 min read</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed">
          The stretch of Interstate 5 between Tacoma and Seattle moves more freight than almost any corridor on the West Coast. It's also one of the easiest places in the country to steal it. National cargo theft losses <strong>surged 60% to $725 million in 2025</strong>. Washington ranks <strong>fifth worst nationally</strong>. And the cities that sit right along this corridor &mdash; Fife, Tukwila, Kent, Tacoma &mdash; have some of the highest property crime rates in the state. Here's what's actually happening, and what warehouse and distribution center operators can do about it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Quick Answer Section -->
    <QuickAnswer
